President Donald J. Trump has announced that the United States will participate in the United States-Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) Summit and the East Asia Summit. He has appointed Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs Robert C. O'Brien as his Special Envoy to both Summits. The United States will reaffirm its commitment to prosperity and security in the Indo-Pacific during the virtual meetings. This year also marks the 5th anniversary of the United States-ASEAN strategic partnership, highlighting the United States' long-standing friendship with ASEAN and its importance in President Trump's vision for a free and open Indo-Pacific.